# Google Drive API Configuration
# Get these values from Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/)

# 1. Create a new project or select existing project
# 2. Enable the Google Drive API
# 3. Create credentials (OAuth 2.0 Client ID for Web application)
# 4. Create an API Key (with Google Drive API restrictions)

# For Astro projects, use PUBLIC_ prefix for client-side environment variables
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Alternative naming (for compatibility with other build systems)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Google API credentials
# 3. Add localhost:4321 (Astro default) to your OAuth 2.0 authorized origins in Google Cloud Console
# 4. Restart your development server after adding these variables